## Findings
### Finding 1: Off-by-one pantry-event count is untested
**Severity**: CRITICAL
**Category**: missing-test
**Location**: src/features/mealplan/mealPlanController.ts:30 / (no test)
**Criticality Score**: 9
**Issue**: No test asserts how many pantryEvent rows are created per entry, so the `i <= days.length` phantom write goes undetected.
**Untested Code**:
```ts
for (let i = 0; i <= days.length; i++) {
  await prisma.pantryEvent.create({ data: { day: days[i], entryId: entry.id } });
}
```
**Why This Matters**: The bug writes 8 rows for a 7-day range (the 8th with day=undefined), corrupting expiring-suggestions ranking. A count assertion fails today and passes after the fix.
#### Test Suggestions
| Option | Approach | Catches | Effort |
| A | Assert pantryEvent.create call count === 7 | Off-by-one directly | LOW |
| B | Assert every created row has a defined day | Phantom undefined day | LOW |
**Recommended**: Option A
**Reasoning**: A call-count assertion pins the exact behavioral contract (one event per day) and is resilient to internal refactors of the loop.
**Recommended Test**:
```ts
it('creates exactly one pantry event per day in range', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const create = vi.spyOn(prisma.pantryEvent, 'create').mockResolvedValue({} as any);
  vi.spyOn(prisma.mealPlanEntry, 'create').mockResolvedValue({ id: 'e1' } as any);
  const req = { body: { recipeId: 'r1', date: '2026-06-08', servings: 2 }, householdId: 'h1' } as any;
  const res = { status: () => res, json: vi.fn() } as any;
  // Act
  await addMealPlanEntry(req, res);
  // Assert
  expect(create).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(7);
});
```
**Test Pattern Reference**: src/features/recipe/recipeController.test.ts:14 — vi.spyOn(prisma.recipe, 'create') with a mocked res.

